- Kafka os configured via application.yml properties
- Properties are printed at startup

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Broker Configs
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
-
- use properties from https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/ (Kap. 3.1)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Topic Configs
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
-
- use properties from https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/ (Kap. 3.2)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Producer Configs
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
- spring.cloud.stream.kafka.binder.producerProperties.<key>: <value>
- use properties from https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/ (Kap. 3.3)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Consumer Configs
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
- spring.cloud.stream.kafka.binder.consumerProperties.<key>: <value>
- use properties from https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/ (Kap. 3.4)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Channel producer/consumer configs
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
- autoCommitOffset etc.
- spring.cloud.stream.kafka.bindings.<channelName>.consumer.<key>: <value>
- set property for all channels:
    spring.cloud.stream.default.<property>: <value>
- use properties from https://github.com/spring-cloud/spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka

